How To Get Therapy When You Can't Leave The HouseEnlarge this image Clare Schneider/NPR Clare Schneider/NPRWith the U.S. at the epicenter of a global pandemic, therapy sessions (or goals to start them) might be taking a back seat.
But as states battle the spread of the coronavirus with stay-at-home orders, people can't attend their regular therapy sessions.
Good news: There are ways to start or continue therapy right where you are.
And just like regular therapy sessions, you can write down some stuff you want to talk about beforehand.
What are the most important things to know about getting therapy right now?